    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>I wanted to match a string that ends with \".*\"\nFor this I had to use the following:</p>\n\n<pre><code>\"^.*\\\\.\\\\*$\"\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Kinda silly if you think about it :D\nHeres what it means. At the start of the string there can be any character zero or more times followed by a dot \".\" followed by a star (*) at the end of the string.</p>\n\n<p>I hope this comes in handy for someone. Thanks for the backslash thing to Fabian.</p>\n"
  }, {
