      "comment_id" : 120936643,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "I have had cases in the past where I had another level of escaping, the result then is \\\\\\\\. After the first layer of escaping that gives \\\\. Then the next layer gives \\. And lastly regex converts that to a simple . I don&#39;t remember exactly when I needed that but maybe it helps with your problem."
