    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Solutions proposed by the other members don't work for me.</p>\n\n<p>But I found this : </p>\n\n<p>to escape a dot in java regexp write <code>[.]</code></p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 10524910,
      "reputation" : 1049,
      "user_id" : 7756218,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 70,
      "profile_image" : "https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-4z5Sf-36o_4/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAB4/k8rtcrfP0Wg/s256-rj/photo.jpg",
      "display_name" : "Deva",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/7756218/deva"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 3,
    "last_activity_date" : 1496731604,
    "creation_date" : 1496731604,
    "answer_id" : 44383099,
    "question_id" : 3674930,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Here is code you can directly copy paste : </p>\n\n<pre><code>String imageName = \"picture1.jpg\";\nString [] imageNameArray = imageName.split(\"\\\\.\");\nfor(int i =0; i&lt; imageNameArray.length ; i++)\n{\n   system.out.println(imageNameArray[i]);\n}\n</code></pre>\n\n<p><strong>And what if mistakenly there are spaces left before or after \".\" in such cases? It's always best practice to consider those spaces also.</strong></p>\n\n<pre><code>String imageName = \"picture1  . jpg\";\nString [] imageNameArray = imageName.split(\"\\\\s*.\\\\s*\");\n    for(int i =0; i&lt; imageNameArray.length ; i++)\n    {\n       system.out.println(imageNameArray[i]);\n    }\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Here, \\\\s* is there to consider the spaces and give you only required splitted strings.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 8516008,
      "reputation" : 1,
      "user_id" : 6384405,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/78b69512781757f5dd2d1cc65af5ad01?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
      "display_name" : "Madhu Gogineni",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/6384405/madhu-gogineni"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1527229006,
    "creation_date" : 1527229006,
    "answer_id" : 50522653,
    "question_id" : 3674930,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>If you want to end check whether your sentence ends with \".<em>\" then you have to add [\\.\\</em>]$ to the end of your pattern.</p>\n"
  }, {
